  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only animals could be that cruel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I think we skip that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know whether it's worth talking about.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Killing-- killing the people off-- just right off the bat for no reason at all.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and which style and which way they killed them, it's-- them guys all had guns with bayonets on them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And were pushing the people around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were march right into the camp then, into Auschwitz, where we was told our luggage would come later on and to be sure everything is marked with our names.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, when we got there, was in, I guess, around noon or afternoon-- I don't know-- we were told to undress and put the clothes in a neat pile so that we'll find it for later on when we get through with it.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the-- the reception in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
